  "title": "Art, Design, Media & Technology (ADMT) Teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></p><p>●      Deliver creative and engaging lessons in Art, Design, Media & Technology.<br />●      Incorporate design thinking, digital tools, and applied learning approaches into the classroom.<br />●      Guide students through the creative process, from ideation to prototyping and showcasing their work.<br />●      Collaborate with colleagues to create interdisciplinary projects that connect with other subject areas.<br />●      Support co-curricular programmes, projects, and events that foster innovation and creative confidence.</p><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><p>●      A recognised degree in Art, Design, Media, Technology, or related fields.</p><p>●      Passion for applied learning, creativity, and interdisciplinary teaching.</p><p>●      Proficiency in relevant design and/or multimedia software.</p><p>●      Strong communication and collaboration skills, with a student-centred approach.</p><p>●      Teaching qualification and experience in a school setting are preferred, but industry professionals with a passion for education are welcome to apply.</p>",
